Kiambu KCPE exam candidates have been urged to focus on their studies, with the test a month away.Nominated MCA Wanjiku wa Kibe said pupils can only achieve their dreams if they excel in their academics.She spoke at St Francis Primary Schools in Gatundu North constituency on Tuesday after presenting geometry sets to candidates. She was accompanied by counsellor Njeri wa Mwangi and lawyer Kimani Kimemia who gave motivational speeches. Today s pupils face fewer challenges because the government has funded the education sector, Kibe said. She warned candidates against cheating. Cheating will not be condoned. It s illegal and will lower the standards of our education. I urge children to use what they ve learnt in class to prove their abilities and avoid any exam irregularity which could land them in jail, Kibe said.